A GOSPEL singer, George Harrison aka GD Harrison has said that more synergy, collaborations, and teamwork should be the order of the day among Nigerian gospel acts. Harrison, who is also a pastor, made this known in a recent chat with The Nation while speaking on his take on the current gospel music space in the country. “The gospel music space is growing rapidly, but I believe there needs to be more synergy, collaboration, and teamwork among Gospel artists if we are to do more as an industry,” he said.   Portable acquires another automobile     I would’ve been a petroleum engineer, says Romeo     Olubukola Bolarinde plans 106 Expressions for June   GD Harrison also spoke about his latest single ‘Onyemmeri’, he said the Igbo-infused track can be translated in English as victor or conqueror. “The Inspiration behind Onyemmeri is gotten directly from the message of the Easter celebration, about the death, burial, and resurrection of Jesus Christ”, said Harrison. GD Harrison is a Nigerian contemporary gospel singer, songwriter, businessman, and technopreneur. He is happily married and a father of two beautiful daughters. He bagged his first degree in Systems Engineering from the University of Lagos.